title: Cylindrical Vase
description:
Tall, cylindrical vase of alabaster with rolled rim and flat bottom. The piece has been pieced together from five smaller fragments.
Condition: Large section of rim and upper part of body missing; numerous chips; incrusted otherwise good.

labels.title: 37.1750E
labels.content: It is not known just what contents were intended to be contained in this tall jar. It could also have been used as a base for a short, roundbottomed jar.
